DataElement.preferredDefinition: Far apart in space, time, or relevance from a point of origin.:An individual who conducts scientific research. In a clinical setting this individual actually conducts and/or supervises the clinical investigation and study-related procedures.  The investigator monitors the safety of the trial subjects and investigational staff (under whose immediate direction an agent is administered or dispensed to a subject).  The investigator collects and analyses data and study documents, and provides reports in compliance with applicable requirements._Coming after all others in time or space or degree or being the only one remaining.:An activity intended to do or accomplish something.  Routinely used as in "number of tries to complete a procedure".:The continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past._Generic value domain for a java datatype that represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision.
